Yeah. So that we can use the reactives that we have. And so with the UI outputs and render UI,

00:53:48.159 --> 00:53:56.159
so that is, it's a valid reactive context. So the main reason why we do that is so that we can

00:53:56.159 --> 00:54:00.560
use those reactives to either decide on what parts of the UI we're going to show,

00:54:00.560 --> 00:54:05.199
